# BeneBots env. SECURITY MODEL:
#   • PUBLIC build (`npm run build` → deployed to Pages) ships ZERO secrets.
#     The public demos are fully canned (no network calls). Do NOT put the
#     worker URL/token in .env or .env.local — Vite inlines BOTH into the
#     public bundle, which would expose the token to anyone.
#   • INTERNAL live mode (`npm run dev`, localhost only) routes the Ask /
#     Stewardship demos through the worker. Put those creds in
#     `.env.development.local` — Vite loads it ONLY in dev, never in `build`.
#
# Never commit any .env* except this example (.gitignore covers them).
# Never give a client-exposed var a real key. `VITE_`-prefixed = shipped to the browser.

# --- INTERNAL LIVE MODE ONLY → put these in .env.development.local (NOT .env) ---
# VITE_WORKER_URL=https://benebots-proxy.YOUR-SUBDOMAIN.workers.dev
# VITE_WORKER_TOKEN=your-shared-secret-token-here

# The Anthropic API key lives ONLY as a Cloudflare Worker secret (server-side):
#   npx wrangler secret put ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
# It must NEVER appear in any VITE_-prefixed var or client file.
